; Unstratified aggregation, KV-index variant (delta-relational-IR R3
; stratification reject, v3-spec-statecell.md §5; a KV index is the
; degenerate aggregate). `balance` merges values keyed by account via
; `add_u32`, but a rule re-derives `balance` from itself (through `carry`),
; so the keyed relation shares the KV index's SCC and is not final before
; the merge runs. The Stratify pass rejects this identically to the
; aggregate case, in all 4 optimization modes, BEFORE the F14 control-flow
; "not yet supported" pre-pass.
#functor add_u32(bound u32 LHS, bound u32 RHS, free u32 Res).
#message credit(u64 Account, u32 Amount).
#local balance(u64 Account, mutable(add_u32) Amount).
#local carry(u64 Account, u32 Amount).
#query get_balance(bound u64 Account, free u32 Amount).

balance(A, N) : credit(A, N).
balance(A, N) : carry(A, N).
carry(A, N) : balance(A, N).

get_balance(A, N) : balance(A, N).
